od Central Nervous System Atypical Teratoid/Rhabdoid Tumor
What are the symptoms of Childhood Central Nervous System Atypical Teratoid/Rhabdoid Tumor ?,"The signs and symptoms of atypical teratoid/rhabdoid tumor are not the same in every patient. Signs and symptoms depend on the following:         - The child's age.    - Where the tumor has formed.        Because atypical teratoid/rhabdoid tumor is fast growing, signs and symptoms may develop quickly and get worse over a period of days or weeks.
